- `0` (Correct, subtraction of equal numbers yields zero)
- `131067` (This is the result of underflow; `35 - 40` would be `-5` in signed arithmetic, but it wraps around in unsigned arithmetic. The binary representation wraps and creates a large positive number when interpreted as `uint32_t`.)
- `0` (Correct, subtraction of equal numbers yields zero)
